                    <div class="card-text">
                        <h2>Java</h2>
                        <p>This course covers the basics of Java, a widely used, object-oriented programming language that powers applications from mobile apps to large-scale enterprise systems. Students will learn about Java syntax, variables, data types, control flow, and methods. A major focus will be on object-oriented programming (OOP) concepts such as classes, inheritance, polymorphism, encapsulation, and abstraction.</p>

                        <div class="card-action">
                            <a href="#" class="button">Read more</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card" id="programming">
                <img src="img/ruby.jpg" alt="">
                <div class="card-content">
                    <div class="card-text">
                        <h2>Ruby</h2>
                        <p>This course introduces students to Ruby, a dynamic, high-level programming language known for its elegant syntax and focus on developer happiness. Students will learn the core principles of Ruby programming including variables, methods, control flow, and blocks. Emphasis will be placed on Ruby's object-oriented nature, with students exploring classes, objects, inheritance, and mix-ins.</p>

                        <div class="card-action">
                            <a href="#" class="button">Read more</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <img src="img/c.jpg" alt="">
                <div class="card-content">
                    <div class="card-text">
                        <h2>C#</h2>
                        <p>This course provides an introduction to C#, a modern, object-oriented language developed by Microsoft and commonly used in Windows development, web applications, and game programming with Unity. Students will learn fundamental programming concepts in C#, including variables, data types, conditionals, loops, and methods. A strong emphasis will be placed on object-oriented programming (OOP), including the use of classes, inheritance, polymorphism, and encapsulation.  </p>
                        <div class="card-action">
